Joint Seminar on Songun Idea Held in Italy 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 10 (KCNA) -- A joint seminar, lecture, photo and book exhibition on the Songun idea were held in Rome on Dec. 29 last year on the occasion of the 14th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army and the 88th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk.
 Exhibited in the venue of the photo and book exhibition  were photos showing the personalities of the three generals of Mt. Paektu as great persons and Kim Jong Il's Songun leadership exploits and photos and books introducing the real picture of Songun Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Miriam Pelegrini Feri, president of the Italian Committee for the Study of the Songun Idea for Independence and Sovereignty, said that the Democratic People's Republic of Korea has firmly defended its socialist system and positively developed the national economy despite the imperialists' all forms of attack and accusation thanks to the Songun politics pursued by Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun politics is the most just political mode for firmly defending the sovereignty of the country from the imperialists' aggression and guaranteeing the economic development and prosperity of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He called on all members of the committee to make an active contribution to defending Korean-style socialism, take an active part in seminars on the Juche idea and the Songun idea and widely disseminate them among broad sections of people.

Abolition of NSL Urged in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 10 (KCNA) -- The Family Movement for Realizing Democracy of south Korea reportedly held the 600th Thursday rally in Seoul on January 5.
 Jo Sun Dok, permanent chairperson of the movement, and other speakers said that this movement has waged an indefatigable struggle for the release of prisoners of conscience and the abolition of the "National Security Law." They went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There have been 600 Thursday rallies up to this date but the evil law remains as it is and the number of prisoners of conscience is on the increase.
 The shortcut to letting all prisoners of conscience in distress return to their families is for all progressive forces to join the ranks of those struggling to achieve democracy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Thursday rally will continue till the NSL is abolished and not a single prisoner of conscience is left in this land.

Young People Vow to Implement Tasks for This Year 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 10 (KCNA) -- The young vanguard met at the open-air theater in Youth Park on Monday to vow to carry through the militant tasks laid down in the joint New Year editorial.
 At the meeting, Kim Kyong Ho, first secretary of the Central Committee of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League, made a report which was followed by speeches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter and speakers said that the young people are a standard-bearer of the vanguard who should stand in the van of the present worthwhile general advance. The young people should join the People's Army to glorify their youthful days with arms and fully discharge their mission in the fields of agriculture, power, coal and metal industries and railway transport, they noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They stressed the need for the youths to successfully build the Paektusan Songun Youth Power Station and other grand monumental edifices and solve scientific and technical problems arising in the building of a great prosperous powerful nation and the need for students to prepare themselves to be competent scientific and technical personnel. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting adopted an appeal to the five million-strong young vanguard across the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The appeal called upon the young people to become fiery fighters in devotedly safeguarding the leader and staunch revolutionary fighters who are thoroughly equipped with the Juche idea and the Songun idea of the Workers' Party of Korea and have acquired the revolutionary soldier spirit as their lifeblood. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The young people, it said, should become performers of feats and young heroes in the vigorous struggle to build an economic power in the 21st century through a high-pitched drive for effecting a great Songun revolutionary surge just as the Korean people brought about the great Chollima upswing after the war to advance toward a socialist power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the meeting were Kim Jung Rin, secretary of the WPK Central Committee, officials concerned and youth and students in the city of Pyongyang.

Rodong Sinmun Calls for Patriotic Movement for National Unity 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 10 (KCNA) -- It is an urgent national task reflecting national desire and the realistic requirements of the development of the reunification movement to make a vigorous patriotic movement for great national unity at present, Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article says, and goes on:
 The patriotic movement for great national unity should be invigorated on a nation-wide scale in order to smash the vicious challenge and obstructive moves of the U.S. and the south Korean conservatives, defend the June 15 era of reunification and achieve the peace and independent reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Only great national unity guarantees peace, reunification and prosperity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is very just and realistic to put forward the patriotic movement for great national unity as one of the three-point patriotic movement to be carried out by the Korean nation this year in the joint New Year editorial. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The patriotic movement for great national unity is the driving force of independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is important for all the Koreans to advance hand in hand for national reunification irrespective of all differences and keep the surging atmosphere of national reconciliation and unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Solidarity among the reunification movement organizations in the north and the south and abroad should be further intensified in the practical reunification movement on the basis of the achievements already made. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The organizational collusion and challenge of the pro-American conservatives in south Korea should be shattered by the great unity of the anti-conservative forces. If the moves of the anti-reunification conservative forces are allowed, national unity and the cause of independent reunification will make no progress. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A new day of independent reunification will be brought earlier in the process of the patriotic movement for great national unity.

Scientists Respond to Joint New Year Editorial 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 10 (KCNA) -- The joint New Year editorial for Juche 95 (2006) says: "The revolution in science and technology should be further intensified so as to fully solve scientific and technical issues arising in the building of a great prosperous powerful nation".
 Upon receiving the editorial, the State Academy of Sciences of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea is concentrating efforts on national cardinal tasks for the development of science and technology and objects to which scientific research achievements should be applied. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Scientists of the academy are engaged in researches into promoting the technical update in different sectors of the national economy including the Chollima Steel Complex. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Geologists have developed a unique underground tomography in years of painstaking efforts, making it possible to put the construction of dams and underground structures on a solid scientific basis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Heat engineers are pushing ahead with the project of replacing the boilers at the Chongchongang Thermal-power Plant with circulating fluidized bed boilers at the final stage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Scientists of the Academy of Agricultural Science, basing themselves on latest scientific and technical achievements, are carrying on the work of applying productive agricultural chemicals and latest technical goods to production in a bold way. And some of them are coming out to co-op farms to rapidly solve issues arising in farming on the spot. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Academy of Medical Science is conducting researches into the application of latest therapeutics to clinical practice.
 Scientists and technicians in other fields are also deepening researches for putting the national economy on a modern and scientific basis and developing ultra-modern technologies.
